@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Delivery — Activity Diagram
start
:Domain event;
:Consume event and deduplicate;
:Evaluate policy\npriority / type / audience;
if (Notify?) then (yes)
  :Load preferences\nquiet hours / channel opt-in;
  :Render localized template;
  :Create inbox item;
  if (Select channels) then (push)
    :Push delivery;
  else (email/sms)
    :Email/SMS delivery;
  endif
  :Record delivery result;
  if (Retry/backoff needed?) then (yes)
    :Schedule retry / digest;
  endif
  :Emit delivery events;
else (no)
  :Drop / record suppressed;
endif
stop

note bottom
Every notification has deduplication key, delivery attempts and final state.
High-priority transactional events should not be batched into digest.
end note
@enduml
